  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To evaluate the efficacy of catheter ablation and rate control in heart failure patients with
      atrial fibrillation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      All patients received either catheter ablation for rhythm control or rate control before
      enrollment, and the investigators do not assign specific interventions to the subjects during
      the study. So this study might be considered to be observational.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
